Antenor of Troy urges that peace be gained by surrendering Helen, the cause of the war. What does Paris do? He foolishly refuses peace on such terms even though it would make his rule sale and his life happy.

Nestor is eager to quiet the quarrel between Achilles and Agamemnom but love in the latter and anger in both still keep their enmity alive. The leaders of the Greeks give way to their passions, their followers pay the penalty.

Quicquid delirant reges, plectunter Achivi.
